                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1709535744",
                        "id": "18076463455454295",
                        "text": "CARBONARA UDON in Tokyo!\n\nYou\u2019ve probably heard of the famous Shin Udon in Shinjuku that is known for their carbonara udon, but we don\u2019t really like waiting in lines \ud83d\ude05\n\nSo we tried out this spot instead and we have to say, it was pretty good!\n\nIt\u2019s the back streets of Harajuku and it\u2019s got such an edgy vibe like all the local streetwear shops around \ud83d\ude4c\ud83c\udffc\n\nWhen we arrived at around 5pm there was no line, so we didn\u2019t have to wait at all!\n\nThe carbonara udon is 950 yen and comes with butter, parmesan bacon and raw egg so you\u2019ve gotta mix it all together to emulsify - be warned, if you hate the thought of eating raw egg then this probably isn\u2019t the place for you \ud83d\ude1d\n\nOverall would totally recommend!\n\nFollow @thefoodinbox for more Japan food and travel \ud83c\udf5c\n\n#carbonaraudon #harajukufood #udon #tokyofood #tokyofoodguide"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
